This paper deals with image segmentation using multiple modalities, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques to improve segmentation accuracy, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of disentangled representations, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with multi-modal processing, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the use of semi-supervised and zero-shot learning, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE).
